Navajo Nation President Jonathan Nez said, "15 to 30% of our people on the Navajo Nation don't have clean running water.
Navajo Nation Police Department sets up road blocks on the Navajo Nation to inform the public about the curfew from 8 p.m. to 5 a.m. as well as hand out pamphlets about COVID-19.
Indian Health Services, the agency responsible for providing federal health services to American Indians and Alaska Natives, serves more than 2.5 million American Indians and Alaska Natives but has only 625 hospital beds.
The Navajo Nation Office of the President and Vice President are urging residents of the Navajo Nation to stay home to prevent the spread of COVID-19.
"The Navajo Nation is a hotspot," said Nez, who added that the Navajo Nation has the third-highest infection rate per capita, behind New York and New Jersey.